{
  "stem": "4189.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And he also had a furniture store, but he managed to get a Visa to come to the United States.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And that just happened just a few months before this incident of the Kristallnacht.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "So what he did, he was smart.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "He did not want to stay in Berlin and wait for his passage to go to America.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "He went to Antwerp, to Belgium, to wait over there to get passage on a boat.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Because in those days, there were no planes.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "You couldn't go to the airport and buy a ticket to fly to America, you had to book a passage on a ship.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And those ships didn't go that frequently, so instead of waiting in Germany, he waited out his turn in Antwerp.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "So my mother got in touch with her brother and told her what had happened and that he has to help us to get out of Berlin.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So they devised a plan that they would take-- there was a train that left every night from Berlin, from the Hauptbahnhof in Berlin, that went from Berlin to Paris with a stop over in Brussels.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And my mother went ahead and she bought a ticket for myself and for my brother, a return ticket to Paris and back.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we were supposed to take this train and go to Brussels.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "When the train stopped in Brussels, my uncle from Belgium would wait for us on the platform and would take us off the train.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Of course, we never intended to go to Paris, that was just to show that we were going to Paris.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
